title: 5-Minute Spicy Stir-Fried Cabbage
directions: 1. Heat the oils in a large skillet set over medium-high heat. Add the ginger and cook, stirring, for 30 seconds.
2. Stir in the cabbage and cook, stirring constantly, until the cabbage is just tender, about 2 minutes.
3. Stir in the chili garlic sauce and soy sauce (or tamari). Season to taste. Serve.
ingredients: 1 (2 lb.) head Napa cabbage, quartered lengthwise & thinly sliced
2 tbsp soy sauce or tamari(for gluten free)
